parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not latch
the seat belt buckle is hard to lock
the seat belt buckle pops out of the seat belt
the seat belt buckle is broken or damaged
the seat belt fails to properly retain occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Repair and Recall Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or refusal of repair and recall services can lead to continued use of faulty seat belts, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Dealership refuses to repair or replace faulty seat belts
unavailability of parts for repair
lack of response from dealership regarding recall
incorrect or incomplete recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speedometer can lead to inaccurate speed readings, which can result in speeding tickets, accidents, or other safety issues.
symptoms: The speedometer needle drops or droops
rubs against the dial
and stops indicating speed
or the needle melts due to heat
causing inaccurate readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission hangs up in third gear when decelerating
and the driver is unable to downshift out of third gear
especially in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the 4x4 transfer case can cause metal particles to get caught in the transmission coolant line, preventing the radiator cooler from functioning properly, which can lead to overheating and engine damage.
symptoms: Metal particles accumulate in the transmission coolant line
blocking the radiator cooler.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake line can cause a complete loss of front braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels to the floor
loss of brake fluid
rust or corrosion visible on the brake line
complete failure of the front braking system.
